1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 11=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,070
Chen, what do we do?

4
00:00:42,390 --> 00:00:43,280
What else can we do?

5
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:44,240
We fall back first.

6
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:45,080
You cover the rear.

7
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:46,110
How loyal.

8
00:00:46,130 --> 00:00:46,870
- Run!
- Hurry!

9
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:47,720
Go, go!

10
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:57,080
Hurry!

11
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:58,110
Hurry up!

12
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,710
- Hurry
- Run!

13
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:03,640
There are wheels under it.

14
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,680
How can legs outrun wheels?

15
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,870
- Keep running!
- Faster!

16
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:07,913
We can't wait to die!

17
00:01:07,924 --> 00:01:09,716
They built a steep slope just for this.
Run!

18
00:01:09,727 --> 00:01:11,040
- Use the grappling gun.
- Move!

19
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:12,200
Pairs of two, retreat!

20
00:01:12,230 --> 00:01:13,120
Yes.

21
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:21,070
Save Chen Youxi and He Shutong first.

22
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,062
Huang Long, what are you doing?

23
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,230
Didn't you hear my order?

24
00:01:30,710 --> 00:01:31,550
Save them.

25
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,520
Hurry!

26
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,710
Everyone, come and help.

27
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:55,040
Why did it stop?

28
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,430
Are you alright?

29
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,040
We're fine.

30
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:00,880
Get up.

31
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:01,880
Get up.

32
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:03,800
Chubby, hurry.

33
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,870
Help Lu across first.

34
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,880
- Go.
- Be careful.

35
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,710
- Chubby.
- Watch out.

36
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:15,470
- Don't look down.
- Careful.

37
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,310
Are you alright?

38
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,840
Chen!

39
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:22,710
Chen! Chen!

40
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:23,800
Chen!

41
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,466
Why didn't you follow my order?

42
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,150
We only have this many grappling guns.

43
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,190
If we saved them,

44
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:34,630
we'd have to die.

45
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,710
Who dies, you or me?

46
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,190
Even if all of you die,

47
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:40,120
Chen Youxi and He Shutong must live.

48
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:45,800
Chen.

49
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,310
Chubby.

50
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:49,280
I'm still alive.

51
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,870
Pull us up.

52
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,240
Chubby.

53
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,560
I thought you were dead.

54
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,840
How did you two end up here?

55
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,680
I'm fine.

56
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,210
How is it?

57
00:04:11,221 --> 00:04:12,334
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

58
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,870
Thank you for saving us.

59
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,560
You're welcome.

60
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,950
Why do you only worry about them?

61
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,160
Worry about me.

62
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:29,440
If something happened to me,
you'd be a widow.

63
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,270
No matter what happens,
take care of Ms. He.

64
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:43,880
Ms. He,

65
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,840
let's go.

66
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:46,230
Alright.

67
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,310
No one takes care of me?

68
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,000
Chubby.

69
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,640
Look at this.

70
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:30,750
My goodness.

71
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:31,720
Good grief.

72
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,063
I've really seen something today.

73
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:35,110
Look at this.

74
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,360
They built a whole palace
inside the tomb.

75
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,430
Good stuff.

76
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,840
Dazhuang.

77
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,390
You guys go light the lamps.

78
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,360
Beautiful.

79
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,360
Good condition.

80
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,160
Let me tell you.

81
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,680
I've sold

82
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,950
several of these before.

83
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,800
What you sold were fakes.

84
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:20,160
These are real.

85
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,000
Chubby,

86
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,840
I'm telling you.

87
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:25,720
This tomb is surely a Tang one.

88
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,960
No doubt about it.

89
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,870
How are you so sure

90
00:06:28,870 --> 00:06:30,160
it's Tang?

91
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,800
These are all Tang characteristics.

92
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:35,230
Listen to me.

93
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,440
Look

94
00:06:36,451 --> 00:06:37,420
at these pottery figures.

95
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,310
Look at this lady.

96
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,510
Her face looks like a steamed bun.

97
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:42,110
Big.

98
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,020
People in the Tang liked that.

99
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,630
They thought it looked good.

100
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:47,600
Plump was beautiful.

101
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:51,950
Plump was beautiful?

102
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,000
I was born in the wrong era.

103
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,390
Brown.

104
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,950
Green.

105
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:12,360
White.

106
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,240
Blue.

107
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:20,630
Tang Sancai doesn't only have
three colors.

108
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:24,430
It uses three primary colors

109
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,390
as glaze colors.

110
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:28,070
By adding metals like copper,
iron, and manganese

111
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,560
and firing it twice at low temperatures,

112
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,630
it can produce many different colors.

113
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,666
Every trade has its specialty.

114
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:38,470
Look at him.

115
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:41,000
Short-sleeved shirt, full beard.

116
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:43,003
That's clearly the attire
of a Central Asian man

117
00:07:43,014 --> 00:07:44,070
from the Tang dynasty.

118
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,630
You can imagine

119
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,560
him riding a camel

120
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,560
along the Silk Road.

121
00:07:51,190 --> 00:07:53,040
Civilizations mingling,
merchants trading.

122
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:55,196
What a prosperous scene
it must have been.

123
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,040
Can you feel it?

124
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,560
No.

125
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,800
Camels only remind me
of the mouthful of sand

126
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,000
I ate in the Nether Ruins.

127
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:17,670
Lu.

128
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:19,303
Come and look in the mirror.

129
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:22,590
Let me see.

130
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:25,800
That's Zhu Bajie.

131
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,430
Let me put you in there.

132
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:30,390
No, don't joke around.

133
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,430
This thing is poisonous.

134
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,510
This is mercury.

135
00:08:32,790 --> 00:08:33,630
Mercury.

136
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,350
I know.

137
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,790
Isn't that just quicksilver?

138
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:37,920
Mercury, huh?

139
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,750
You idiot, no sense of measure.

140
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,680
Lu.

141
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:46,990
Look at this.

142
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,030
All these brushes, ink, paper,
and inkstones.

143
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:51,600
It looks like a place
where people painted.

144
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:53,390
What kind of place is this?

145
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:58,390
I reckon this was a painting class

146
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,670
in the Tang dynasty.

147
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:03,350
Look, look.

148
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,840
A kid sitting here.

149
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,480
A parent sitting beside him.

150
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:09,510
The teacher strolling around.

151
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,390
There would probably be a young lady

152
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,600
sitting there as a model.

153
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,550
Beautiful.

154
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:32,843
Look at these musician figurines.

155
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,630
They wear inner shirts
and outer silk shawls,

156
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:37,000
holding musical instruments.

157
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:40,200
They recreate
the court's music and dance life.

158
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:43,440
Placing musician figurines
around the coffin

159
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:45,360
suggests the tomb owner

160
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,120
had a love for music.

161
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,030
It seems this should be

162
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:52,150
a Tang imperial tomb chamber.

163
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:55,790
Very elaborate.

164
00:09:58,510 --> 00:09:59,720
Impressive.

165
00:10:00,750 --> 00:10:01,750
Usually, I've only heard

166
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:05,360
of the emperor's four-sided coffin.

167
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:07,870
Today, I've seen
the empress's four-sided one.

168
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:10,320
This big coffin is grand.

169
00:10:10,547 --> 00:10:12,100
What's an emperor's four-sided coffin?

170
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,750
It means the emperor's coffin

171
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:18,630
has dragons carved on all four sides,

172
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,440
surrounding him

173
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,390
for good fortune.

174
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:23,470
But

175
00:10:24,150 --> 00:10:25,630
there are no dragons here.

176
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:27,240
Only phoenixes were carved.

177
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:28,750
That's the key.

178
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:30,870
Phoenixes usually represent women.

179
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,320
So, I reckon

180
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:33,480
inside this coffin

181
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:36,750
must be a woman of great status.

182
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Either a princess

183
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,440
or a consort.

184
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:41,510
Judging by the structure of this tomb,

185
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,630
with such a four-sided coffin
placed here,

186
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:47,000
the person inside
should be the tomb owner.

187
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,670
Go see if that door can be opened.

188
00:10:58,680 --> 00:10:59,550
Open the coffin.

189
00:10:59,630 --> 00:11:00,470
Don't move.

190
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:02,350
Chubby.

191
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,440
Light the lamp.

192
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:05,960
Lu, give me the candle.

193
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:06,800
Why?

194
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,440
There are so many lamps already lit.

195
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:09,790
Let's save some.

196
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:10,870
We still have to go back.

197
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:11,790
I'm telling you.

198
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:14,790
Our ancestors' rules must be followed.

199
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:27,030
Even if we're not exploring secrets,

200
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:28,750
lighting the candle puts us at ease.

201
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:29,990
Good.

202
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,910
Chen, come on.

203
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:32,870
Open the coffin.

204
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,720
One, two, three.

205
00:12:02,150 --> 00:12:04,670
Why is it empty? There's nothing inside.

206
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,806
Where are the burial goods?

207
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:07,470
Were they stolen?

208
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,630
Chen,

209
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:10,960
look.

210
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,360
This eyeball pattern

211
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,270
is exactly the same
as the one on your back.

212
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:30,840
That's what I wanted.

213
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,320
Don't move.

214
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,790
There's nothing
in the tomb owner's coffin

215
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:37,000
except a stone box.

216
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,750
Very suspicious.
There must be a mechanism.

217
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,440
Everyone, be careful.

218
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:54,960
Huang, that side can be opened.

219
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:08,376
Huang Long, what are you doing?

220
00:13:09,959 --> 00:13:11,046
- Don't move.
- Don't move.

221
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:13,630
Huang Long, put the box down.

222
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,470
That's the mechanism.

223
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,120
- Huang Long.
- In your dreams.

224
00:13:18,496 --> 00:13:19,910
Find something with the same weight

225
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:21,280
- to replace it.
- Okay.

226
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:22,590
Try this.

227
00:13:24,130 --> 00:13:25,000
Not enough.

228
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:25,920
Here.

229
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,790
Chen, look above!

230
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:50,440
Huang Long, stop!

231
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,750
Chen, Ms. He, are you alright?

232
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:52,630
We're fine.

233
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:53,920
Lu.

234
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:56,110
Huang Long.

235
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,120
Give me the box.

236
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,670
Why should I give it to you?

237
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:03,399
What difference does it make

238
00:14:03,410 --> 00:14:04,360
whether it's with you

239
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,550
or with me?

240
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,480
If there's no difference,

241
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:09,150
why must I give it to you?

242
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,630
Huang, the door opened.

243
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:12,790
Everyone,

244
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,440
we can't come here for nothing.

245
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:16,750
Take everything

246
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:17,960
that looks valuable.

247
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,800
Yes.

248
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:29,360
Huang Long, don't forget.

249
00:14:29,650 --> 00:14:30,790
Your mission is to assist me.

250
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:31,630
You're wrong.

251
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:34,240
My mission is to find the item

252
00:14:34,630 --> 00:14:35,470
and bring it back.

253
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,480
You don't really think

254
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,390
the boss put all his hopes

255
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:41,120
on you alone, do you?

256
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,320
Huang Long!

257
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,566
I'll go check if that door
can still be opened.

258
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:48,670
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

259
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:54,030
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

260
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:59,670
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

261
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:06,820
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

262
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:18,400
♪La la♪

263
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,140
♪No line divides the border♪

264
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:29,920
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

265
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,290
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

266
00:16:32,290 --> 00:16:34,980
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

267
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,190
♪Hey hey hey♪

268
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:41,340
♪Hey hey hey♪

269
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:44,990
♪Hey hey♪

270
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:46,140
♪Hey hey♪

271
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,680
♪Hey hey♪

272
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:54,510
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

273
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:58,810
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

274
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:03,310
♪No difference between you and me♪

275
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:05,920
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

276
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:08,130
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

277
00:17:08,350 --> 00:17:10,630
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

278
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:16,350
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

279
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:21,200
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

280
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:26,050
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

281
00:17:26,050 --> 00:17:28,140
♪This is our world♪

282
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:33,170
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

283
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:40,260
♪In a blink, to forever♪
